Chretien nowhere gives any description of the nature of the Round Table . 
With him , it is an institution . 
Layamon in Brut and Wace in Le Roman de Brut are more specific in their accounts of this remarkable piece of furniture . 
From their descriptions , and from other sources in Welsh and Irish literature , it is reasonable to suppose that the Round Table had a place in primitive Celtic folk lore . 
